2011/3/22 Ralph Castain <span dir="ltr">&lt;<a href="mailto:rhc@open-mpi.org">rhc@open-mpi.org</a>&gt;</span><br><blockquote class="gmail_quote" style="margin:0 0 0 .8ex;border-left:1px #ccc solid;padding-left:1ex;"><div style="word-wrap:break-word">
The problem is here:<div><br></div><div><div class="im"><div>                                      /* Pack the faulty vpid */</div><div>                                        if (ORTE_SUCCESS != (rc = opal_dss.pack(buffer, &amp;proc, 1, ORTE_NAME))) {</div>
<div>                                            ORTE_ERROR_LOG(rc);</div><div>                                            goto CLEANUP;</div><div>                                        }</div><div><br></div></div><div>The variable proc is apparently a pointer to orte_process_name_t. You therefore should have packed it like this:</div>
<div class="im"><div><br></div><div><div>                                        /* Pack the faulty vpid */</div><div>                                        if (ORTE_SUCCESS != (rc = opal_dss.pack(buffer, proc, 1, ORTE_NAME))) {</div>
<div>                                            ORTE_ERROR_LOG(rc);</div><div>                                            goto CLEANUP;</div><div>                                        }</div></div><div><br></div></div>
<div>i.e.., without the &amp; in front. Accordingly, the problem was that the HNP was getting garbage for the process name, and thus finding NULL at the specified locations.</div><div><br></div><div>Just for testing, you might want to print out the received process name to ensure your communication is correct :-)</div>
<div><br></div><div><br></div><div><div><div></div><div class="h5"><div>On Mar 22, 2011, at 5:58 AM, Hugo Meyer wrote:</div><br></div></div><blockquote type="cite"><div><div></div><div class="h5"><div class="gmail_quote">
